1ZLhStlxI9k|title=Whatcha Packin: Vanessa Vanjie Mateo {{!}} Season 10 Episode 1 {{!}} RuPaul's Drag Race Season 10|publisher=[[VH1]]|date=May 26, 2018|accessdate=September 22, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|2018\n|''Cosmo Queens''\n|Cosmopolitan Series\n|<ref>{{cite av media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_ZpEzIIZcFs|title=Vanessa Mateo {{!}} Cosmo Queens {{!}} Cosmopolitan|publisher=[[YouTube]]|date=August 19, 2018|accessdate=September 22, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|2019\n|''The Pit Stop''\n|Guest\n|<ref>{{cite av media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=240EfdsuPRs|title=The Pit Stop Season 4 Episode 7: Miss Vanjie Spills the Tea {{!}} RuPaul\u2019s Drag Race All Stars 4|publisher=[[YouTube]]|date=January 26, 2019|accessdate=September 22, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|2019\n|''Reading Queens''\n|Episode: \"Miss Vanjie\"\n|<ref>{{cite av media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LTeEyu5j-qM|title=Miss Vanjie: Reading Queens with Psychic Char Margolis|publisher=[[YouTube]]|date=May 16, 2019|accessdate=January 3, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|2019\n|''Follow Me''\n|Episode: \"Miss Vanjie\"\n|<ref>{{cite av media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-ZhBzbLD9YU|title=FOLLOW ME: Miss Vanjie|publisher=[[YouTube]]|date=June 17, 2019|accessdate=January 2, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|2019, 2020\n|''Be$tie$ For Ca$h''\n|With [[Silky Nutmeg Ganache]], later with [[Alexis Mateo]]\n|<ref>{{cite av media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oNsGavhG7pU&t|title=BESTIES FOR CASH - Holiday Edition with Silky and Vanjie|publisher=[[YouTube]]|date=December 17, 2019|accessdate=December 20, 2019}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Discography==\n===Singles===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Title\n|-\n| 2018\n| scope=\"row\" | \"I'm Vanjie\"\n|}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n* 2019: Competition Contestant - [[People's Choice Award]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/09/e-peoples-choice-awards-finalists-complete-list-1202710461/|title=E! People\u2019s Choice Awards Finalists Announced; Voting Open Through Oct. 18 \u2013 Complete List|last=Evans|first=Greg|date=4 September 2019|website=Deadline|access-date=13 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|Vanessa Vanjie Mateo}}\n* [https://www.imdb.com/name/nm9720348/ Jos\u00e9 Cancel] on [[IMDb]]\n\n{{RuPaul's Drag Race}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mateo, Vanessa Vanjie}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1991 births]]\n[[Category:American drag queens]]\n[[Category:LGBT people from Florida]]\n[[Category:People from Tampa, Florida]]\n[[Category:Puerto Rican drag queens]]\n[[Category:RuPaul's Drag Race contestants|Vanessa Vanjie Mateo]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=March 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Vanessa Vanjie Mateo\n| image              = Rupaul Dragcon 2018-252 (42030783392).jpg\n| caption            = Vanessa Vanjie Mateo at [[RuPaul's DragCon LA]] in 2018\n| birth_name         = Jos\u00e9 Cancel\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|df=no|1991|10|3}}\n| birth_place        = [[Puerto Rico]]\n| occupation         = [[Drag queen]]\n| known_for          = Competing on ''[[RuPaul's Drag Race]]''\n| website            = https://www.vanessavanjie.com\n}}\n\n'''Vanessa Vanjie Mateo''', sometimes known as '''Miss Vanjie''' or simply '''Vanjie''', is the [[stage name]] of '''Jos\u00e9 Cancel''',<ref>{{Cite new|url=https://metro.co.uk/2018/08/24/drag-race-viral-sensation-miss-vanjie-wants-you-to-stop-saying-vanjie-during-sex-7879421/|title=Drag Race viral sensation Miss Vanjie wants you to stop saying 'Vanjie' during sex|first=Emma |last=Kelly|date=August 24, 2018|accessdate= February 3, 2019|work=[[Metro (British newspaper)|Metro]]|location=UK| archivedate=January 25, 2019|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20190125073420/https://metro.co.uk/2018/08/24/drag-race-viral-sensation-miss-vanjie-wants-you-to-stop-saying-vanjie-during-sex-7879421/|url-status=live}}</ref> an American [[Drag queen|drag performer]] known for competing on the [[RuPaul's Drag Race (season 10)|tenth]] season of ''[[RuPaul's Drag Race]]'' and placing fifth on the [[RuPaul's Drag Race (season 11)|eleventh]] season of the show.\n\n== Early life ==\nCancel is of [[Puerto Rico|Puerto Rican]] descent. He started doing drag when ''Drag Race'' [[RuPaul's Drag Race (season 3)|season three]] and ''[[RuPaul's Drag Race All Stars (season 1)|All Stars]]'' alumna [[Alexis Mateo]] hired him as a backup dancer.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bustle.com/p/how-vanessa-vanjie-mateos-drag-mom-alexis-helped-the-rupauls-drag-race-star-bounce-back-from-that-heartbreaking-elimination-8569404|title=How Vanessa Vanjie Mateo's Drag Mom Came to Her Rescue After That 'RuPaul' Elimination|last=Koch|first=Drew|work=Bustle|access-date=April 22, 2018|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/pride/8258218/vanessa-vanjie-mateo-drag-race-interview|title='RuPaul's Drag Race:' Vanessa Vanjie Mateo Talks Meeting Christina Aguilera, Her Favorite Local Queen & More|work=Billboard|access-date=April 21, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n===''RuPaul's Drag Race''===\n[[File:Dragcon3-SUN-9 (47942923151).jpg|thumb|left|upright|Vanessa Vanjie Mateo in 2019]]\nVanessa Vanjie Mateo was announced as one of the fourteen contestants competing for the crown on the [[RuPaul's Drag Race (season 10)|tenth season]] of ''[[RuPaul's Drag Race]]'', which premiered on March 22, 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.out.com/television/2018/2/16/rupauls-drag-race-season-10-premiering-week-after-all-stars|title='RuPaul's Drag Race' Season 10 is Premiering a Week After 'All Stars'|date=February 16, 2018|access-date=April 21, 2018|language=en}}</ref> She was eliminated in the first episode, after [[lip sync]]ing to [[Christina Aguilera]]'s \"[[Ain't No Other Man]]\" against competitor Kalorie Karbdashian Williams, while Aguilera was the guest judge.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.goldderby.com/article/2018/rupauls-drag-race-10-episode-1-elimination-interview-vanessa-vanjie-mateo-10s-across-the-board-video/|title=\u2018RuPaul\u2019s Drag Race\u2019 10 episode 1 elimination interview: Vanessa Vanjie Mateo dishes '10s Across the Board' [WATCH]|last=Sheehan|first=Paul|date=March 28, 2018|work=GoldDerby|access-date=April 21, 2018|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nAs she walked backwards off the stage, her parting words were \"Miss Vanjie... Miss Vanjie... Miss... Vanjie\", which later became an [[internet meme]]. \"Miss Vanjie\" was tweeted by many, including several by [[RuPaul]], as well as [[Michelle Visage]] and [[Kathy Griffin]]. The meme was also edited into clips of various movies, TV shows, and even on dating apps, including ''[[The Simpsons]]'', ''[[Pok\u00e9mon (anime)|Pok\u00e9mon]]'', [[Grindr]], and ''[[The Shining (film)|The Shining]]''.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/pride/8280564/rupauls-drag-race-miss-vanjie-memes|title='RuPaul's Drag Race:' The Very Best of the 'Miss Vanjie' Memes|work=Billboard|access-date=April 21, 2018}}</ref> The YouTube channel [[WatchMojo.com|Watchmojo]]'s spin-off channel, ''MsMojo'', made a top ten list of the memes, making it the first ''Drag Race'' related ''MsMojo'' video based on one specific contestant.<ref>{{Citation|last=MsMojo|title=Top 10 Best Miss Vanjie Memes|date=2018-04-20|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1-odXTOjy_g|access-date=2018-10-14}}</ref>\n\nThe \"Miss Vanjie\" catchphrase was said by [[Rylan Clark-Neal]] while commenting on the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2018]] first semi-final broadcast during the presentation of [[Eleni Foureira]] from [[Cyprus]]; he also said it in reference to [[Montenegro]] singer [[Vanja Radovanovi\u0107]], whose name resembles Miss Vanjie's.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://metro.co.uk/2018/05/08/rylan-clark-wins-eurovision-semi-final-miss-vanjie-drag-race-gag-7531516/|title=Rylan Clark wins Eurovision semi-final with Miss Vanjie Drag Race gag|date=May 8, 2018|work=Metro|access-date=May 9, 2018|language=en-GB}}</ref> [[RuPaul]] wore a \"Vanjie\" necklace during the [[Time 100 Gala]] red carpet.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/pride/8390243/rupaul-miss-vanjie-necklace-time-100-red-carpet-photo|title=RuPaul Donned a 'Miss Vanjie' Necklace on Time 100 Gala Red Carpet|work=Billboard|access-date=2018-05-24}}</ref> The catchphrase was also referenced in multiple further episodes of ''Drag Race'' season ten. A [[Snapchat]] filter of Vanessa's runway look was made available the day after the season ten reunion.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.newnownext.com/miss-vanjie-snapchat-filter-drag-race/06/2018/?xrs=_s.tw_RPDR|title=There's Now A Miss Vanjie Snapchat Filter|work=LOGO News|access-date=2018-06-23}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Vanessa Vanjie Mateo at Dragcon 2019 by dvsross.jpg|thumb|upright|Vanessa Vanjie Mateo, 2019]]\n\nOn January 24, 2019, Mateo was announced as one of the fifteen competitors of [[RuPaul's Drag Race (season 11)|season 11]] of ''RuPaul's Drag Race''.<ref name=\"Season11\">{{cite news |last1=Rudolph |first1=Christopher |title=Meet the Queens of \"RuPaul\u2019s Drag Race\" Season 11 |url=http://www.newnownext.com/rupauls-drag-race-season-11-queens-cast/01/2019/?utm=share_twitter |accessdate=24 January 2019 |publisher=New Now Next |date=January 24, 2019}}</ref> She was in the bottom two for episodes nine and ten, and won both lip syncs against [[Plastique Tiara]] and [[Shuga Cain]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/pride/8509397/drag-race-lip-sync-fantasia-hood-boy|title=Lip-Sync Herstory: 5 Things You Didn't Know About Fantasia's 'Hood Boy'|website=Billboard|access-date=2019-05-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.goldderby.com/article/2019/rupauls-drag-race-season-11-episode-9-plastique-tiara-eliminated/|title=\u2018RuPaul\u2019s Drag Race\u2019: Was the right queen eliminated in episode 9 \u2018L.A.D.P.\u2019? [POLL]|last=Sheehan|first=Paul|last2=Sheehan|first2=Paul|date=2019-04-26|website=GoldDerby|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/pride/8510803/rupauls-drag-race-power-ranking-season-11-episode-10|title='RuPaul's Drag Race' Power Ranking Season 11: Episode 10|website=Billboard|access-date=2019-05-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tvline.com/2019/05/02/rupauls-drag-race-recap-shuga-cain-eliminated-season-11-episode-10/|title=RuPaul's Drag Race Recap: Which Queen Disappeared Like Magic?|last=Swift|first=Andy|last2=Swift|first2=Andy|date=2019-05-03|website=TVLine|language=en|access-date=2019-05-10}}</ref> She was eliminated by [[Brooke Lynn Hytes]] in the penultimate week in episode twelve, and placed fifth.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.goldderby.com/article/2019/rupauls-drag-race-season-11-episode-12-vanessa-vanjie-mateo-eliminated/|title=\u2018RuPaul\u2019s Drag Race\u2019: Was the right queen eliminated in episode 12 \u2018Queens Everywhere\u2019? [POLL]|last=Sheehan|first=Paul|last2=Sheehan|first2=Paul|date=2019-05-17|website=GoldDerby|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://culturess.com/2019/05/17/rupauls-drag-race-season-11-episode-12-review-canada-vs-vanjie/|title=RuPaul\u2019s Drag Race review: Canada vs. Vanjie|date=2019-05-17|website=Culturess|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://instinctmagazine.com/post/rupauls-drag-race-season-11-who-deserves-to-win-the-most/|title=\u2018RPDR\u2019 Season 11 Has One Clear Winner \u2022 Instinct Magazine|date=2019-05-17|website=Instinct Magazine|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-17}}</ref>\n\n===Post ''Drag Race''===\nMateo was featured on the September 2018 issue cover of ''[[Gay Times]]''.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.gaytimes.co.uk/culture/112418/yaaas-honey-see-drag-races-miss-vanjie-like-youve-never-seen-before/|title=Yaaas honey! See Drag Race's Miss Vanjie like you've never seen before|date=2018-08-24|work=Gay Times|access-date=2018-08-24|language=en-GB}}</ref> She appeared with [[Nina Bo'nina Brown]] for two episodes of the [[World of Wonder (company)|WOWPresents]] internet series \"Fashion Photo RuView\" on November 3 and 17, 2018, filling in for [[Sutan Amrull|Raja]] and [[Raven (drag queen)|Raven]].<ref>{{Citation|last=WOWPresents|title=FASHION PHOTO RUVIEW: Dancing Queen with Miss Vanjie and Nina Bo'nina Brown!|date=2018-11-03|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WozfpRfEzR8&t=329s|access-date=2018-11-03}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|last=WOWPresents|title=FASHION PHOTO RUVIEW: Vanessa Vanjie and Nina Bo'nina Brown!|date=2018-11-17|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XbuLimDqLxU|access-date=2018-11-22}}</ref> She appeared with [[Silky Nutmeg Ganache]] and [[Derrick Barry]] for an episode of the [[Germany's Next Topmodel (season 14)|fourteenth season]] of ''[[Germany's Next Topmodel]]'' in 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.watson.de/!248126877|title=Die Dragqueens sind zur\u00fcck bei \"GNTM\"! Alles, was ihr zu Miss Vanjie & Co. wissen m\u00fcsst|website=watson.de|language=de|access-date=2019-05-07}}</ref> On May 12, 2019, Mateo was sponsored by [[Chips Ahoy!]] for a social media post for [[Mother's Day]], which got homophobic backlash.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lgbtqnation.com/2019/05/conservatives-got-triggered-mothers-day-commercial-chips-ahoy/|title=Conservatives got triggered by a Mothers Day commercial from Chips Ahoy!|last=Bollinger|first=Alex|date=2019-05-13|website=www.lgbtqnation.com|access-date=2019-05-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dailywire.com/news/47152/watch-chips-ahoy-uses-famed-drag-queen-mothers-day-amanda-prestigiacomo|title=WATCH: Chips Ahoy! Uses Famed Drag Queen For Mother's Day Ad, Mocks Critics: 'They're Big Mad'|last=Am|last2=May 14|first2=apresto|date=2019-05-14|website=Daily Wire|language=en|access-date=2019-05-15|last3=Views|first3=2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Music ===\nMateo released her first single, \"I'm Vanjie\", on June 21, 2018.<ref>{{Citation|title=I'm Vanjie - Single by Vanessa Vanjie Mateo|date=2018-06-21|url=https://itunes.apple.com/au/album/im-vanjie-single/1400991726|language=en-AU|access-date=2018-06-21}}</ref>\n\nShe appeared in the music video for [[Iggy Azalea|Iggy Azalea's]] \"[[Sally Walker (song)|Sally Walker]]\" on March 14, 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2Gy8eGr7AfM|title=Iggy Azalea - Sally Walker (Official Music Video)|date=2019-03-14|language=en|access-date=2019-03-15}}</ref> She performed as a backup dancer to the song on [[Jimmy Kimmel Live!]] in April 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.newnownext.com/miss-vanjie-las-vegas-iggy-azalea-jimmy-kimmel/04/2019/|title=Miss Vanjie Slays Live Las Vegas Performance With Iggy Azalea|date=2019-04-06|work=Newnownext|language=en|access-date=2019-04-07}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.idolator.com/7740825/iggy-azalea-delivers-first-sally-walker-performance-on-jimmy-kimmel?firefox=1|title=Iggy Azalea Delivers First \"Sally Walker\" Performance On \u2018Jimmy Kimmel\u2019|date=2019-04-05|work=Idolator|language=en|access-date=2019-04-07}}</ref> Mateo was also in the video for Azalea's \"[[Started (Iggy Azalea song)|Started]]\" with [[Trixie Mattel]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtonblade.com/2019/05/06/watch-iggy-azalea-recruits-trixie-mattel-and-vanessa-vanjie-mateo-for-started-music-video/|title=Watch: Iggy Azalea recruits Trixie Mattel and Vanessa Vanjie Mateo for 'Started' music video|date=2019-05-06|website=Washington Blade: Gay News, Politics, LGBT Rights|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.newnownext.com/miss-vanjie-trixie-mattel-iggy-azalea-started-video/05/2019/|title=Miss Vanjie, Trixie Mattel Are Femme Fatales in Iggy Azalea\u2018s \"Started\" Video {{!}} NewNowNext|website=www.newnownext.com|access-date=2019-05-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pride.com/music/2019/5/03/iggy-azalea-trixie-mattel-kill-their-sugar-daddies-new-video|title=Iggy Azalea & Trixie Mattel Kill Their Sugar Daddies in New Video|date=2019-05-03|website=www.pride.com|language=en|access-date=2019-05-10}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n=== Television ===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" | Role\n! scope=\"col\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2018\n| scope=\"row\" | [[RuPaul's Drag Race (season 10)|''RuPaul's Drag Race'']]\n| rowspan=\"9\" |Herself\n| Contestant (14th place)\n|-\n| 2018\n| scope=\"row\" | ''RuPaul's Drag Race: Untucked''\n|\n|-\n| 2019\n| scope=\"row\" | [[RuPaul's Drag Race (season 11)|''RuPaul's Drag Race'']]\n| Contestant (5th place)\n|-\n|2019\n|''RuPaul's Drag Race: Untucked''\n|\n|-\n| 2019\n| scope=\"row\" | ''[[Jimmy Kimmel Live!]]''\n| Backup dancer\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[Germany's Next Topmodel (season 14)|Germany's Next Topmodel]]''\n| Guest\n|-\n| 2020\n| ''[[AJ and the Queen]]''\n| Guest appearance\n|-\n| 2020\n| scope=\"row\" | [[RuPaul's Drag Race (season 12)|''RuPaul's Drag Race'']]\n| Guest\n|-\n| 2020\n| ''[[RuPaul's Celebrity Drag Race]]''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2019/10/rupauls-celebrity-drag-race-new-show|title=RuPaul Announces Drag Race Spin-Off Featuring All-Celebrity Competitors|last=Desta|first=Yohana|website=Vanity Fair|language=en|access-date=2019-10-22}}</ref>\n| Mentor\n|}\n\n===Music videos===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" | Role\n|-\n| 2019\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Iggy Azalea]] \u2013 \"[[Sally Walker (song)|Sally Walker]]\"\n| Funeral attendee\n|-\n| 2019\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Iggy Azalea]] \u2013 \"[[Started (song)|Started]]\"\n| Real Estate Agent\n|}\n=== Web series ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Title\n!Role\n!Notes\n! {{Tooltip|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n|2018, 2019\n|''Queen to Queen''\n| rowspan=\"8\" |Herself\n|With Kalorie Karbdashian Williams, later with [[Silky Nutmeg Ganache]] and [[A'keria Chanel Davenport]]\n|<ref>{{cite av me