sion on History & Culture, ASIN B0000CPBFX\n* Mumtaz Husain Bazmi, (1996), ''Zindanon se aivanon tak'', al-Hamd Pablikeshanz, ASIN B0000CRPOT\n* Prof. Dr. Khuhro. Amir Ahmed, (2012)\"Personality as a Factor in Foreign Policy Making (a case study of Pak: US Relations during Benazir Bhutto periods)\", printed and published by The Lambert Academic Publishing (LAP) Company, Saarbr\u00fccken, Germany under its {{ISBN|978-3-659-29380-1}}, published on 3 November 2012.\n* Prof. Dr. Khuhro. Amir Ahmed,(2013) \"Benazir Bhutto (Life & trends in foreign policy)\" published and printed by The Lambert Academic Publishing (LAP) Company, Saarbr\u00fccken, Germany under its {{ISBN|978-3-659-38290-1}}, published on 6 May 2013.\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Benazir Bhutto}}\n{{Wikiquote|Benazir Bhutto}}\n* {{C-SPAN|benazirbhutto}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-ppo}}\n{{s-bef|rows=2|before=[[Nusrat Bhutto]]}}\n{{s-ttl|rows=2|title=Leader of the [[Pakistan Peoples Party]]|years=1982\u20132007<br />{{small|Acting: 1982\u20131984}}}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Bilawal Bhutto Zardari]]}}\n|-\n{{s-aft|after=[[Asif Ali Zardari]]}}\n|-\n{{s-off}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Muhammad Khan Junejo]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Prime Minister of Pakistan]]|years=1988\u20131990}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Ghulam Mustafa Jatoi]]<br />{{small|Acting}}}}\n|-\n{{s-bef|before=[[Mahbub ul Haq]]<br />{{small|Acting}}}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Minister of Finance (Pakistan)|Minister of Finance]]|years=1988\u20131990}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Sartaj Aziz]]}}\n|-\n{{s-bef|before=[[Mahmoud Haroon]]<br />{{small|Acting}}}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Minister of Defence (Pakistan)|Minister of Defence]]|years=1988\u20131990}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Ghous Ali Shah]]}}\n|-\n{{s-bef|before=[[Khan Abdul Wali Khan]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Leader of the Opposition (Pakistan)|Leader of the Opposition]]|years=1990\u20131993}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Nawaz Sharif]]}}\n|-\n{{s-bef|before=[[Moeenuddin Ahmad Qureshi]]<br />{{small|Acting}}}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Prime Minister of Pakistan]]|years=1993\u20131996}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Malik Meraj Khalid]]<br />{{small|Acting}}}}\n|-\n{{s-bef|before=[[Syed Babar Ali]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Minister of Finance (Pakistan)|Minister of Finance]]|years=1994\u20131996}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Naveed Qamar]]}}\n|-\n{{s-bef|before=[[Nawaz Sharif]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Leader of the Opposition (Pakistan)|Leader of the Opposition]]|years=1996\u20131999}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Fazl-ur-Rehman (politician)|Fazl-ur-Rehman]]}}\n|-\n{{s-dip}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Marich Man Singh Shrestha]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Chairperson of [[South Asian Association for Regional Cooperation|SAARC]]|years=1988}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Maumoon Abdul Gayoom]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n{{Prime Ministers of Pakistan}}\n{{Finance Minister of Pakistan}}\n{{Bhuttoism}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bhutto, Benazir}}\n[[Category:Benazir Bhutto]]\n[[Category:1953 births]]\n[[Category:2007 deaths]]\n[[Category:20th-century Pakistani writers]]\n[[Category:20th-century women rulers]]\n[[Category:21st-century Pakistani writers]]\n[[Category:21st-century politicians]]\n[[Category:21st-century women politicians]]\n[[Category:Alumni of Lady Margaret Hall, Oxford]]\n[[Category:Alumni of St Catherine's College, Oxford]]\n[[Category:Assassinated Pakistani politicians]]\n[[Category:Bhutto family]]\n[[Category:Children of national leaders]]\n[[Category:Children of Prime Ministers of Pakistan]]\n[[Category:Convent of Jesus and Mary, Karachi alumni]]\n[[Category:Convent of Jesus and Mary, Murree alumni]]\n[[Category:Female defence ministers]]\n[[Category:Female heads of government]]\n[[Category:Heads of regimes who were later imprisoned]]\n[[Category:Islamic democracy activists]]\n[[Category:Karachi Grammar School alumni]]\n[[Category:Leaders of the Opposition (Pakistan)]]\n[[Category:Pakistani anti-communists]]\n[[Category:Pakistani exiles]]\n[[Category:Pakistani expatriates in the United Arab Emirates]]\n[[Category:Pakistani financiers]]\n[[Category:Pakistani people of Iranian descent]]\n[[Category:P