{"title_page": "Leah Hackett", "text_new": "{{Notability|Biographies|date=January 2016}}\n\n{{Infobox person\n| name                  = Leah Hackett\n| image                 =\n| imagesize             =\n| caption               =\n| birthname             = \n| birth_date            = {{Birth date and age|1985|8|15|df=y}}\n| birth_place           = [[Bolton]], England\n| death_date            =\n| death_place           =\n| occupation            = Actress\n| children = 1\n| years_active          = \n2006&ndash;present\n}}\n\n'''Leah Hackett'''  (born 15 August 1985), is an English [[actress]], most notable for her role as [[Tina Reilly]] (n\u00e9e McQueen) in ''[[Hollyoaks]]''.\n\n==Early life==\nHackett was born in [[Bolton]], [[Greater Manchester]] to a mixed race ( English mother / African/American father) father and an English mother. She worked in [[Tyldesley]] Library as a teenager. She attended Tyldesley Primary School before moving to [[Fred Longworth High School]]. She later attended [[Winstanley College]] and went on to get a place at [[Liverpool Institute for Performing Arts]].<ref name=\"Interview with Leah Hackett\">{{cite news|title=Interview with Leah Hackett|url=http://www.wlct.org.uk/Culture/linconline/leahhackett.htm|publisher=Wigan Leisure & Culture Trust|accessdate=5 April 2009|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110405193218/http://www.wlct.org.uk/Culture/linconline/leahhackett.htm|archivedate=5 April 2011|df=}}</ref>\n\nShe appeared in Reemer's video for the single ''Maniac''.<ref name=\"Leah Hackett stars in music video\">{{cite news|title=Leah Hackett stars in music video|url=http://www.channel4.com/entertainment/tv/microsites/H/hollyoaks/news/previous/08/04/080430_gallery.html|publisher=Channel 4|date=30 April 2008|accessdate=5 April 2009|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081002013027/http://www.channel4.com/entertainment/tv/microsites/H/hollyoaks/news/previous/08/04/080430_gallery.html|archivedate=2 October 2008}}</ref>\n==Personal life==\nIn January 2020, she annouced she was pregnant with her first child due April 2020. On April 3rd 2020, she gave birth to a daughter, Skylar.\n\n==Career==\nHackett played timid [[Tina Reilly]] in [[Channel 4]] soap ''[[Hollyoaks]]''. She played the role for over two years between 3 August 2006, until her character's death on 17 October 2008.\nShe reprised the role for one episode on 20 November 2014.\n\n\nShe also appeared in the Liverpool Nativity on 16 December 2007 as a [[shepherdess]]. In July 2008, Hackett was the face selected to launch the [[Polaroid Corporation|Polaroid]] [[Polaroid Corporation#Mobile printers|PoGo]].<ref name=\"Polaroid launches a wallet-sized printer that prints your mobile phone snaps in seconds\">[https://www.gettyimages.ca/detail/news-photo/hollyoaks-actress-leah-hackett-launches-the-polaroid-pogo-news-photo/834647164 Getty Images]</ref> She also appeared in a series of videos promoting the Year of Food and Farming where she milks a cow, shears sheep, collects eggs and makes an ice cream at Blaze Farm in [[Cheshire]].<ref name=\"Hollyoaks star takes to the farm\">{{cite news|title=Hollyoaks star takes to the farm|url=http://www.thinkfoodandfarming.org.uk/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=20&Itemid=34|publisher=Think Food and Farming|date=4 July 2008|accessdate=19 January 2016}}</ref> She appeared in a [[pantomime]] (Dick Whittington), at [[Buxton Opera House]] and she played Alice Witzwarren. She appeared as Clare Saunders in an episode of ''Doctors'', titled \"The Mathematics of Marriage\", which aired 15 December 2010.{{citation needed|date=January 2016}}\n\n==Other TV appearances==\n*2010 - DOCTORS (Clare Saunders) - (BBC)\n*2011 - THE CASE (Tamsin Hatfield) - Lime Pictures Ltd (ITV) \n*2012 - DOCTORS (Michaela Everett) - (BBC)\n*2012 - GOOD COP (Laura) - BBC Drama Productions\n*2012-present - FOUR O'CLOCK CLUB - (WPC Rowe) CBBC\n*2014 - CORONATION STREET (WPC Swanson)\n\n==Stage appearances==\n* November 2010, ''Pub'' (musical drama), Royal Exchange, Manchester \n* June to July 2013, ''Manchester - The Massacre'' (a promenade performance drama splicing the Peterloo Massacre of 1819 and the Hacienda Movement of 1989), Library Theatre company\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Television===\n{| border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 90%;\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#B0C4DE\" align=\"center\"\n! Year(s)\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| 2006&ndash;2008\n| ''[[Hollyoaks]]''\n| [[Tina Reilly]] (n\u00e9e McQueen)\n| [[Channel 4]]\n|-\n| 2012-present \n| ''[[4 O'Clock Club]]''\n| WPC Rowe\n| Series 2-8\n|- \n| 2014\n| ''[[Coronation Street]]''\n| PC Stanley\n| [[ITV (TV network)|ITV]], 1 episode \n|- \n| 2017\n| ''[[The Break (BBC TV series)|The Break]]''<ref>https://www.bbc.co.uk/bbcthree/item/d6a78121-6b43-4640-a46c-9ccd66c368c0</ref>\n| Lisa\n| [[BBC]], 1 episode\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb name|id=2625071|name=Leah Hackett}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hackett, Leah}}\n[[Category:1985 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:British television actresses]]\n[[Category:People from Bolton]]\n[[Category:Black British actresses]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Greater Manchester]]\n[[Category:English soap opera actresses]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the Liverpool Institute for Performing Arts]]\n[[Category:English people of African-American descent]]\n", "text_old": "{{Notability|Biographies|date=January 2016}}\n\n{{Infobox person\n| name                  = Leah Hackett\n| image                 =\n| imagesize             =\n| caption               =\n| birthname             = \n| birth_date            = {{Birth date and age|1985|8|15|df=y}}\n| birth_place           = [[Bolton]], England\n| death_date            =\n| death_place           =\n| occupation            = Actress\n| years_active          = 2006&ndash;present\n}}\n\n'''Leah Hackett'''  (born 15 August 1985), is an English [[actress]], most notable for her role as [[Tina Reilly]] (n\u00e9e McQueen) in ''[[Hollyoaks]]''.\n\n==Early life==\nHackett was born in [[Bolton]], [[Greater Manchester]] to a mixed race ( English mother / African/American father) father and an English mother. She worked in [[Tyldesley]] Library as a teenager. She attended Tyldesley Primary School before moving to [[Fred Longworth High School]]. She later attended [[Winstanley College]] and went on to get a place at [[Liverpool Institute for Performing Arts]].<ref name=\"Interview with Leah Hackett\">{{cite news|title=Interview with Leah Hackett|url=http://www.wlct.org.uk/Culture/linconline/leahhackett.htm|publisher=Wigan Leisure & Culture Trust|accessdate=5 April 2009|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110405193218/http://www.wlct.org.uk/Culture/linconline/leahhackett.htm|archivedate=5 April 2011|df=}}</ref>\n\nShe appeared in Reemer's video for the single ''Maniac''.<ref name=\"Leah Hackett stars in music video\">{{cite news|title=Leah Hackett stars in music video|url=http://www.channel4.com/entertainment/tv/microsites/H/hollyoaks/news/previous/08/04/080430_gallery.html|publisher=Channel 4|date=30 April 2008|accessdate=5 April 2009|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081002013027/http://www.channel4.com/entertainment/tv/microsites/H/hollyoaks/news/previous/08/04/080430_gallery.html|archivedate=2 October 2008}}</ref>\n==Personal life==\nIn January 2020, she annouced she was pregnant with her first child due April 2020.\n\n==Career==\nHackett played timid [[Tina Reilly]] in [[Channel 4]] soap ''[[Hollyoaks]]''. She played the role for over two years between 3 August 2006, until her character's death on 17 October 2008.\nShe reprised the role for one episode on 20 November 2014.\n\n\nShe also appeared in the Liverpool Nativity on 16 December 2007 as a [[shepherdess]]. In July 2008, Hackett was the face selected to launch the [[Polaroid Corporation|Polaroid]] [[Polaroid Corporation#Mobile printers|PoGo]].<ref name=\"Polaroid launches a wallet-sized printer that prints your mobile phone snaps in seconds\">[https://www.gettyimages.ca/detail/news-photo/hollyoaks-actress-leah-hackett-launches-the-polaroid-pogo-news-photo/834647164 Getty Images]</ref> She also appeared in a series of videos promoting the Year of Food and Farming where she milks a cow, shears sheep, collects eggs and makes an ice cream at Blaze Farm in [[Cheshire]].<ref name=\"Hollyoaks star takes to the farm\">{{cite news|title=Hollyoaks star takes to the farm|url=http://www.thinkfoodandfarming.org.uk/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=20&Itemid=34|publisher=Think Food and Farming|date=4 July 2008|accessdate=19 January 2016}}</ref> She appeared in a [[pantomime]] (Dick Whittington), at [[Buxton Opera House]] and she played Alice Witzwarren. She appeared as Clare Saunders in an episode of ''Doctors'', titled \"The Mathematics of Marriage\", which aired 15 December 2010.{{citation needed|date=January 2016}}\n\n==Other TV appearances==\n*2010 - DOCTORS (Clare Saunders) - (BBC)\n*2011 - THE CASE (Tamsin Hatfield) - Lime Pictures Ltd (ITV) \n*2012 - DOCTORS (Michaela Everett) - (BBC)\n*2012 - GOOD COP (Laura) - BBC Drama Productions\n*2012-present - FOUR O'CLOCK CLUB - (WPC Rowe) CBBC\n*2014 - CORONATION STREET (WPC Swanson)\n\n==Stage appearances==\n* November 2010, ''Pub'' (musical drama), Royal Exchange, Manchester \n* June to July 2013, ''Manchester - The Massacre'' (a promenade performance drama splicing the Peterloo Massacre of 1819 and the Hacienda Movement of 1989), Library Theatre company\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Television===\n{| border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 90%;\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#B0C4DE\" align=\"center\"\n! Year(s)\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| 